### Render content for signed-out users with <Show />

Source: https://github.com/clerk/clerk-docs/blob/main/docs/guides/configure/session-tasks.mdx

Use when='signed-out' to display content to unauthenticated users. Pending sessions are treated as signed-out by default.

```tsx
export default function Page() {
  return (
    <Show when="signed-out">
      <p>Users that are signed-out or pending will see this.</p>
    </Show>
  )
}
```

```tsx
export default function Page() {
  return (
    <Show when="signed-out" treatPendingAsSignedOut={false}>
      <p>Users that are signed-out will see this.</p>
    </Show>
  )
}
```

--------------------------------

### handleUnauthenticated()

Source: https://github.com/clerk/clerk-docs/blob/main/docs/reference/objects/clerk.mdx

Handles a 401 response from the Frontend API by refreshing the client and session object accordingly. Use this function to manage unauthenticated states in your application.

```APIDOC
## handleUnauthenticated()

### Description
Handles a 401 response from Frontend API by refreshing the client and session object accordingly.

### Method
Function

### Signature
```typescript
function handleUnauthenticated(opts?: { broadcast: boolean }): Promise<unknown>
```

### Parameters

#### opts
- **Type**: `{ broadcast: boolean }`
- **Required**: No
- **Description**: Optional configuration object for handling unauthenticated responses.

##### opts.broadcast
- **Type**: `boolean`
- **Required**: No
- **Description**: Whether to broadcast the unauthenticated event.

### Return Value
- **Type**: `Promise<unknown>`
- **Description**: A promise that resolves when the unauthenticated response is handled.
```

--------------------------------

### Protect routes with auth.protect() in Next.js middleware

Source: https://github.com/clerk/clerk-docs/blob/main/docs/guides/configure/session-tasks.mdx

Use auth.protect() in clerkMiddleware to redirect unauthenticated and pending users to the sign-in page. Pending users will be prompted to complete session tasks before gaining access.

```typescript
import { clerkMiddleware, createRouteMatcher } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'

const isProtectedRoute = createRouteMatcher(['/dashboard(.*)', '/forum(.*)'])

export default clerkMiddleware(async (auth, req) => {
  // pending users won't be able to access protected routes
  // and will be redirected to the sign-in page
  if (isProtectedRoute(req)) await auth.protect()
})

export const config = {
  matcher: [
    // Skip Next.js internals and all static files, unless found in search params
    '/((?!_next|[^?]*\.(?:html?|css|js(?!on)|jpe?g|webp|png|gif|svg|ttf|woff2?|ico|csv|docx?|xlsx?|zip|webmanifest)).*)',
    // Always run for API routes
    '/(api|trpc)(.*)',
  ],
}
```

--------------------------------

### Protect Page and Access User Data in Astro Component

Source: https://github.com/clerk/clerk-docs/blob/main/docs/guides/users/reading.astro.mdx

Use auth() to check authentication status and redirect unauthenticated users, then use currentUser() to access user details for server-side rendering. The currentUser() call counts toward Backend API rate limits.

```astro
---
// Use `locals.auth()` to access `isAuthenticated` and the user's ID
const { isAuthenticated, userId } = Astro.locals.auth()

// Protect the route by checking if the user is signed in
if (!isAuthenticated) {
  return Astro.redirect('/login')
}

// Get the Backend User object when you need access to the user's information
const user = await Astro.locals.currentUser()
---

<!-- Use `user` to render user details or create UI elements -->
<div>Welcome, {user.firstName}!</div>
```

### Overview

Source: https://github.com/clerk/clerk-docs/blob/main/docs/guides/development/custom-flows/authentication/email-sms-otp.mdx

Clerk supports passwordless authentication, which allows users to sign in and sign up without remembering a password. Instead, users receive a one-time password (OTP) via email or phone to authenticate themselves.

